narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class is fantastic. You work hard but learn a significant and impressive amount of hebrew
Ayala is wonderful, Hebrew is an interesting language, and the class isn't too difficult at all--definitely take it.

Modern Hebrew 110 is a course that will take you from knowing no hebrew to being able to confidently hold a basic conversation in a few months! Yes! Take it! Sign up now! You won't regret it! You learn so much in a semester and it is so practical!
I would describe it as an introductory course to Hebrew. I would recommend it strongly.
Yes. The course is super fun and it teaches you a lot for an L1 course.There is a lot of homework, but I think that's the only way to make students learn.
